        "creation_date": 1690484874,
        "body": "<p>If you do not have a jar file:<\/p>\n<pre><code>javac file.java\njava file\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>If your jar file and source code (.java) file are on the same dir you can run following command to compile it.<\/p>\n<p>If you have a Mac :<\/p>\n<pre><code>javac -cp .:lib.jar Main.java\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>If you have a windows :<\/p>\n<pre><code>javac -cp .;lib.jar Main.java\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>This command will create byte code (.class file) for the specific .java file.\nThen executing,<\/p>\n<pre><code>java -cp .:external-library.jar Main\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>will execute that script.<\/p>\n<p>Here,<\/p>\n<p>-cp stands for class path which is the path to the .jar file location.<\/p>\n<p>javac stands for java compiler. it compiles the source code to byte code.<\/p>\n",
